  QL_BalladOfHeroZora_Desc:
    contents:
      - text: "The scattered One-Hit Obliterator led me to a\nlocation where a stone monument with a map of\ntrials appeared. Kass's song seems related...\n\nOne, "
      - control:
          kind: set_colour
          colour: red
      - text: "find what the light's path shows"
      - control:
          kind: reset_colour
      - text: ".\nTwo, "
      - control:
          kind: set_colour
          colour: red
      - text: conquer the ancient foes
      - control:
          kind: reset_colour
      - text: ".\nThree, "
      - control:
          kind: set_colour
          colour: red
      - text: chase rings of the waterfall
      - control:
          kind: reset_colour
      - text: ".\nChampion, the trials call!\n\nI still have "
      - control:
          kind: set_colour
          colour: red
      - text: three
      - control:
          kind: reset_colour
      - text: " trials to complete."
  QL_BalladOfHeroZora_Finish:
    contents:
      - text: "I defeated the phantasm of Waterblight\nGanon, which was born from my own\nmemories and fears.\n\nKass's composition, entitled "
      - control:
          kind: set_colour
          colour: red
      - text: "Champion Mipha's\nSong"
      - control:
          kind: reset_colour
      - text: ", was so true and moving that it allowed\nme to visualize a memory from 100 years ago.\n\nBy conquering the trial, my sacred power has\nincreased and Mipha's Grace has become\nmore efficient than ever."
